<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%>
	   <a name=10287309951664></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f10287309951664><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=14&mid=10287309951664>RE: charming undead</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=14&mid=10287309951664#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=153229><span id=Sage>Falrinth</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>32 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Aug 7th 10:47 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>As mentioned it is random (until you get the level 59 or 60 (can't remember) fixed duration charm). To counter the inherent risk in this I recommend:<br><br>* re-casting charm while the pet is still charmed (depending on max duration of the charm you are using - I normally do it every 30 seconds to be sure with the level 54 charm)<br><br>* keep screaming terror memmed and use it if charm breaks (it is fast to cast and enables you to then re-charm)<br><br>* always have a way to invis yourself if charming so you can break charm at will by casting invis (circlet of shadows rocks for this)<br><br>* when you are slaying stay away from your temporary pet and tell it to sit away from you when not fighting so you have time to deal with it if charm breaks (i.e. don't let it wander around next to you as pets tend to do)<br><br>As mentioned above charm is really best used to break camps with multiple undead. It is pretty dicey and you should not rely on a charmed mob as a proper pet - rather use to break and for crowd control. Keep in mind we get Dire Charm at level 60 class AA (quite an achievement) - now THAT is the business!<br>&nbsp;<br>Falrinth Twysted<br>65 Dark Elven Arch Lich<br>Second Age<br>Cazic Thule</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
