	   <tr><td colspan=2>Our charm line of spells is along the lines of the root line of spells. You just dont know when its gonna break..&nbsp;&nbsp;:) The best way of using the spell really is only limited by your imagination. The most poplur is to charm an undead creature and just wreak havoc on little green mobs and stuff, and the second is to create a temporary pet, wheres if you had your pet he would have caused all kind of aggro and train problems. Case in point you charm an undead mob to help split a spawn where if you summoned a pet its quite possible you would be dealing with 2 mobs instead of one. Charm one undead and have it attack its buddy.<br><br>The only problem is, once that charm wears off, now that mob is pissed off at you, so you better have root and charm memmed. Each spell has a max duration but again its random. You weigh the Risk/Reward over using the spell. As far as charming a ghoul, if the ghoul can cast spells, then you just charmed a mob that can assist you and cast spells on your attackers. Good Luck<br><br>Azelus Azedon Warlock<br>Conclave of The Damned<br>7TH Hammer<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
