<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%>
	   <a name=102750684566088></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f102750684566088><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=14&mid=102750684566088>RE: question</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=14&mid=102750684566088#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=153229><span id=Sage>Falrinth</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>32 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Jul 24th 6:46 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Sphoenix you have been missing out on a rare gem of transportation in Norrath - and after reading this post I hope you check it out and post your thoughts on it. The Timourous Deep teleporter room (sometimes called the &quot;pots room&quot;) is a place that has escaped the attention of many people because it is (a) initially quite hard to find and far away (b) in a zone that it has not been possible to bind in at times (though you can bind there now) and (c) it's ...erm...guarded by an underwater dragon that kills everyone.<br> <br>It is located in the far south west of Timorous Deep - virtually on the bottom left corner of any zone map. The loc is -12260, 4665, -277. Use DMF to run down there and stay invisable the whole way. As you near the area you will see 4 pillars rising from the sea. I suggest that the best place to bind for most casters is in fact ON TOP of one of these pillars - the reason for this will soon become clear. Once at the pillars swim down under the sea and you will see a square opening in the sea floor at the centre point of the 4 pillars. Swim down and enter and float into the room beneath with DMF. Here you will find a room filled with fire pots and an NPC skeleton who tells the tale of the sea dragon I referred to in an earlier post - there are no MOBs here unless of course the sea dragon is around (in which case you won't be ;P). <br><br>Once you have entered the room you cannot get out again without using one of the teleporters - this is why it is wise to bind above on a pillar above the sea so you have to option to journey within TD as well (although with Levant you can do the same thing really - even if bound inside the porter room itself - as I am).<br><br>So, once bound on a pillar or in the room itself you can left click on a pot and it will port you to the following locations:<br><br>North Left:(fire on floor) to Grobb (entrance) <br>North Center:(6 side gray) to Oggok (entrance) <br>North Right:(6 side tall) to Erudin (near dock) <br>East Left:(6 side gray) to Neriak Commons (entrance) <br>East Center:(4 side wood) to Greater Faydark (under Kelethin) <br>East Right:(6 side rust) to Northern Felwithe (entrance) <br>South Left:(Brown box) to Halas(near dock) <br>South Center:(Dark with blue) to East Freeport (on dock) <br>South Right:(tall gold vase) to Cabilis West (entrance) <br>West Left:(White marble) to South Kaladim (entrance) <br>West Center:(Lava Lamp) to Akannon (entrance) <br>West Right:(torch stand) to Rivervale (entrance) <br><br>Make sure you are invis when you use these teleporters because they will often deposit you by NPCs that may be KOS to you! However, mostly you will come out very near a zone line in the relevant destination zone.<br><br>From a quick scan of the locations of these teleporters you will see that this place is no use if you play in Luclin or Velious a lot - BUT when in the old world and wanting a way to Kunark it totally OWNS. Combined with a hammer of overthere and Levant you can get almost anywhere in the old world so fast people will wonder how you do it ;P Very good when getting ready to gate up to Hate etc and you need to get a stone from Neriak then get to GFay spires - or if wanting to go anywhere in Kunark (since once you can make your way around Cabilis no where in Kunark is that hard to get to either). I intentionally spend a fair bit of time in the old world simply because of the ease of travel that comes from use of the teleporter room.........but obviously sometimes you have to go to Velious and Luclin too and bind there :(<br><br>Be careful of the sea dragon Faydedar. He is KOS to all (as far as I know) and red to me at 58th. The general idea is to bind here but only stay in the teleporter room very briefly in between &quot;jumps&quot; to other locations.<br><br>Check it out - enjoy! There is no reason why any caster (melees can't be bound there) who can bind and gate shouldn't check this out and do it......oh other than for fear of the dragon of course ;P<br><br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Wed Jul 24 06:37:53 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br>Falrinth Twysted<br>65 Dark Elven Arch Lich<br>Second Age<br>Cazic Thule</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
