	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f102707635337434><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=14&mid=102707635337434>RE: Howling Stones</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=14&mid=102707635337434#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=153229><span id=Sage>Falrinth</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>32 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Jul 19th 7:11 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.85]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Howling stones solo is brutal if you slip up. If the inital break in goes poorly your trip to HS can be a brief one. I only got into this fairly recently (at 57th) and suspect that at 55th it might be a bit tough to do effectively. If you do try it keep in mind:<br><br>- when you first go there you MAY not be KOS (if you are OK in the Overthere Outpost you are OK in HS). If that is the case many mobs there won't even attack you (but con to be sure each time) and you should use this non KOS time to get the lay of the land and look around a bit. As an Iksar you are likely to be KOS straight out - as a DE I was not.<br><br>- when you first zone in ensure that you are invis (ideally invis to undead but this will be tricky if KOS to the scorpions outside), have manaskin on, DMF on and all your usual armour buffs. Do not move at all when you zone in - check out what's up before you do. You should not be aggroed if you don't move on zoning in - but move one inch and BAM!<br><br>- when you get there you will know from previous posts that there are 2 wanderers (normally undead but not always). Break using ST/root/charm/shackle etc etc BUT if it gets ugly drop over the edge and look for a clear landing spot as you float down to FD then /q to wipe aggro. When you return you can use the teleporter pad in the room below to take you straight up to the top room for another try at breaking it.<br><br>- respawn in HS is about 20 mins so keep that in mind for the wanderers assuming you have broken them. Ideally have a desktop stopwatch.<br><br>- when you start pulling golems in the zone in room the pathing is the key to it. If you pull with doom (or just root straight out then doom) make sure you move to the opposite side of the square pagoda zone in spot once the golem (hopefully just one ;P) starts coming for you. This requires that it walk around the pegoda to get to you rather than straight at you.<br><br>- if a golem reaches you corner run straight across to the other side again. Again the pathing here will help you but learn where the pit traps are....<br><br>- you may struggle at 55th to keep mana up and take down the mobs with any real efficiency but if you stack doom, splurt, ignite and bond re-apply etc you might actually manage. Again if it gets ugly drop over the edge (hence why you always want DMF here)<br><br>- you may find it easier to solo in the room beneath but if you can break the top room and get into the swing of things its good<br><br>- ALWAYS have Harmshield memed<br><br>- the first time you go it might be a good plan to have someone to back you up or bail you out if it goes poorly.<br><br>I hope these pointers help and will be interested to hear back from you as to whether it is in fact managable at 55th.<br><br>EDIT: I think that you can manage the area below at level 55 pulling singles and using a pet with shackle of spirit on undead mobs. I was there last night and totally owned the undead mobs in this way - your pet can tank fine one shackle is on with maybe only one BoD needed to heal him.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Fri Jul 26 07:07:46 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br>Falrinth Twysted<br>65 Dark Elven Arch Lich<br>Second Age<br>Cazic Thule</td></tr>
