	   <tr><td colspan=2>Couple of things you can do. Providing you have the cash. ALWAYS buy your Lifetap and Pet Spells first. At lvl 7 the first thing you want to do is cast a lvl 1 pet *Cavorting Bones*, stand somewhere safe, and cast your Lifespike and Ward Undead Spells on your pet over, and over, and over until you max out the Magic Skill in each area of magic. *Alteration, Abjuration, Evocation, Conjuration and Divination.* Just load up lvl 1 spells and cast away until you run out of mana and repeat the process for about an hour. <br><br>Once you max out your skill in each area of magic you will get alot less fizzles, and a fizzle can mean the difference between life and death. Be patient and remember at low lvls your pet is basically a DoT but can not tank for long by himself which means sometimes you may need to step in and take a few hits, then Lifetap them back.<br><br>Dont get frustrated, its always tough at lower lvls but it gets easier the higher you get. The Idea is to snare the target with a speed reducing DoT *Darkness Line*, Fear the target So its running away SLOWLY, Send in the Pet to start the beating, Cast a Few DoT's to assist in the hp's loss and ultimate death of the mob, and try to get in the habit in your career of refreshing Darkness and Fear BEFORE they run out. In General once Darkness sticks, it will be on until it runs&nbsp;&nbsp;its full course. <br><br>Azelus Azedon 60 Warlock<br>Conclave of The Damned<br>7TH Hammer<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
