	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.85]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Beware fellow necros. For those of you bound in Timorous Deep teleporter room (for the excellent access it gives you to all of old world Norath) - BEWARE. I saw a new NPC skeleton there last night who, when hailed, told a tale of how he had died at the hands of the water dragon because he spent too long in the teleporter room. I don't know how this may manifest itself (perhaps out of the fire or through the walls??) because I didn't hang around to find out but there were lots of corpses there......lots. Something to be aware of even though personally I don't plan to change my bind spot ;P Just move fast if that is where you are bound. I assume VI has done this to prevent too many people binding in this spot - if you don't know about it already and want to know why it is THE best place to bind for necros (and other non porting casters) in all of Norath then read the section on Timorous Deep to find out or travel there and see for yourselves. This could lead to some interesting raiding opportunities - since now it may be that the water dragon comes to you instead of needing to be tracked....nice.<br><br>Since this is principally a strategy forum I better mention one. I am surprised by the number of casters who are unaware that when standing in a corner with your back firmly against a wall you can almost always cast a spell without interruption even with mobs beating on you - hence the reason why, if aggroed, it is a good idea to Harmshield and back into a corner in preparation for FD or gate. This has saved me innumerable times in dungeons.<br><br>One final point: roleplay a bit - don't tell other caster classes the above tips ;P<br>&nbsp;<br>Falrinth Twysted<br>65 Dark Elven Arch Lich<br>Second Age<br>Cazic Thule</td></tr>
