	   <tr><td colspan=2>Sphoenix, thanks for your post which was, in part I believe, in response to mine below. I am sure you meant 1 yellow in 6 hours not one blue and suspect that is about as good as it gets at level 58 or so. A very large number of the mobs in SD are green to me or light blue so persoanlly I have no real interest in that at 58th. Otters are excellent and their drops are better than those in Katta IMO - unless someone tells me Katta is significantly better than 1 yellow in 5 hours at 58+ i'm going hard out on Otters for a while until I get bored and go adventuring again (usually for months until I decide I need some exp - it isn't after all a race to 60 though when you are close as we are now the temptation to cane it to 60th for the outstanding spells is high).<br><br>The best place to pull in ME is just to the right of the zone to DS (as you walk out of the corridor to the right that is). Sit up there medding etc and pull with doom from the field then fear the mob as it reached the base of the hill (it will run around back and forth below you) - I don't much like ME solo however because the trains are EVIL and the mobs have a lot of hps - some with high resists and they run really fast ;P I'm my experience (and I welcome the views of others on this to expand my repertoire) if you want exp at 58+ and you are mad and brave go to HS (Charasis) and be prepared to get butched if you slip up - or if you are more into a safe steady slog Otters in CS, Raptors in TD and anything that moves the Grey (except the MResist worms and Rockfiends). None of which is as good exp wise, fun wise and loot wise as a decent team in CT.<br>&nbsp;<br>Falrinth Twysted<br>65 Dark Elven Arch Lich<br>Second Age<br>Cazic Thule</td></tr>
