	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>In reference to Maidens Eye Probably or arguably the safest spot for pulling the Goranga's is where I call &quot;Rock Central&quot;. If you come from DP and look straight out from ME youll see a big rock on your right and another rock straight ahead that has a group of Goranga Lookouts. If you setup your camp somewhere in the middle of those 2 rocks, close to the tree, you should be ok. If you go there and look at the zone youll know what Im talking about.<br><br>When people talk about trains they are &quot;Generally&quot; refering to Vampire Bats, Coterie, and Xiu Xaui. Most people setup camp on the hill right next to the DP Zone, on the right hand side. That is a bad mistake. Case in point. People who hunt or attempt to hunt that undead outpost with the bats, Coterie and Xia Xaui are actually hunting right behind you if you camp on that hill. When the inevitable Druid_09 pulls from that outpost and gets some adds, they are gonna be making a Bee Line for that zone. And you happen to be sitting/medding right in the middle of where the &quot;Undead Train From Hell&quot; is coming... Im telling you from experience... That train has no brakes.... If you are sitting on that hill when that train comes by 1 of 2 things are gonna happen.<br><br>One- Xia Xaui Hits You For 135 Points Of Damage!!<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;   Xia Xaui Hits You For 131 Points of Damage!!<br>     Xia Xaui Hits You For 109 Points Of Damage!!<br>     Xia Xaui Bashes You For 56 Points Of Damage!<br>     You Writh In The Grip Of Agony!!<br>     You Have Taken 434 Points Of Damage!!<br>     A Vampyre Bat Bites You For 110 Points Of Damage!!<br>     A Vampyre Bat Attempts To Bite You!!'<br>     You Dodge!!<br>     A Coterie Crushes You For 129 Points Of Damage!!<br>     You Are Bleeding!!<br><br> LOADING PLEASE WAIT.......<br><br>Number 2- The Train Runs Past You Semming as If its still chasing Druid_09. Unbeknownst to you, once Druid_09 Zones, any mob that was anywhere near you when it came by is now coming for you....<br>Lol sometimes this zone is weird... I was sitting Medding, Partnered up with a Shammy friend when someone shouts &quot;OMG Everybody ZONE!!! Zone NOW!!!&quot; I say /ooc Which Zone is The Train Coming To?  Someone says /shout F#$KING ZONE!!!! At the time it was about 23 people in the zone. I kid you not, I saw PC after PC running past me spamming /y. So me being the Heroe Necromancer, I decide to stay to see what the commotion was. You know, throw in a DD here, Slow Down a Mob there. I turn around and immdiately all brain activity CEASED for like 3 secs. THE BIGGEST TRAIN I have ever seen in my EQ Life. It was EASILY Every Mob in the Damn Zone. From the Toilers, to the Goranga's, Xiu Xaui, Coterie, Vampyre Bats, Ravenous Beasts, Mind Burrowers you name it. Imagine if you will the Running of the Bulls. Now Imagine 1 person running from like 100 Bulls, and the Bulls are right on that ARSE. <br><br>This Wizard was Running For All he Was Worth. It was horriffic yet funny as hell at the same time. Like 18 People died, Then even more people died who were just simply zoning in and passing thru. Both undead and regular NPC's were at the zone in. Rather than cast FD, I just casted QVoX and ran through some of it to get through.  Apparently what happened was the wizard tried to solo the undead spot and got some adds. He ran all around the zone looking for the exit, while unknowingly aggroing everything in the zone.<br><br>FYI Every Mob in that Zone has AT LEAAST 6k hp's the Goranga's have right about 6, while the undead mobs and those leech things have at least 7.5k. One more thing, try not to pull the Goranga Lookouts that are huddled at the farthest rock. At 60 if you pull 1, all 4 are coming and sometimes if you cast FD immdiately they still coming right at ya. If you get in that situation just announce the /ooc Train to DP! And get out of Dodge. You could try to ST them, but they have High MR, so if you get a resist they still coming.  Sorry for the Long Story But had to let you know about good ol ME. Loot Sucks but Exp is real good, and 85% of the time its 5pp drops....  :)<br><br>Hope this helps someone.<br><br>Azelus Azedon 60 Warlock <br>Conclave of The Damned <br>7TH Hammer<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
