	   <tr><td colspan=2>Humans take least amount of experience to level and can generally travel more widely unmolested. OK so they are not as bright as Erudites, Gnomes and Dark Elvess but there are a hell of a lot of INT items - especially at high level so I wouldn't let that worry you. The only major bummer about being human is you don't look as infinitely cool as, shall we say, Dark Elves - particularly in black and red.<br><br>Once you get your sight spells even as a human you will see fine and there are items that can assist in that way as well.<br><br>If you've made your way to 21st level why change? Race in my view makes sod all difference to necros in the long run even if initially the INT bonus some races get does in fact make a difference. Just out level your peers with your lower exp requirement ;P<br>&nbsp;<br>Falrinth Twysted<br>65 Dark Elven Arch Lich<br>Second Age<br>Cazic Thule</td></tr>
