	   <tr><td colspan=2>If I were you, I wouldnt hold my breath. Necromancers are not a group oriented class first of all. Second, you will almost always get passed up on for magicians. In My Opinion Magicians have more to offer a group than a Necro does. To many of our spells are self only and the ones that can been used in a group appear to not really serve a purpose. The Scent line of Debuffs for example. Necromancers were intended to be a Self Sufficient class because they are to Evil and Repulsive to associate with any other non Evil Classes. <br><br>I didnt mean for this to be a long winded thread but If this is your first character and your first exp with EQ and you want a group oriented character, I would suggest you make a character of another class. The very plus side to this is you can solo up to 60 quite easily and you can take on Camps/Mobs that were intended for groups. Others will be pissed watching you solo Mobs that a full group is having trouble with. It pisses them all off, and to hell with em all. No single other class has as many utility spells as you making you the most efficicent soloing machine in the game.... Need I compare?<br><br>You can Snare and Fear (Magicians Cant), You can Charm like an Enchanter, Dots, AOE Spells, Heal Yourself, Heal Others, Mezz, Ultimate Undead Line of Spells, and can solo with quite efficiency. I personally hate grouping. Always have, and always will. Nothing worse than being in a group and the Cleric is trying to DD like a Wizard, Enchanter is playing Tank, and the Tank is Pulling when everybody is OOM and then gets pissed when he dies from no heals. There is always one idiot that leads to everyone elses death, and personally I like to be responsible for my own. <br><br>If you want to group all the time I suggest you make a Cleric, Warrior, or some other group oriented class. Your gonna have a long hard life trying to group frequently as a Necro.<br><br>Azelus Azedon 60 Warlock<br>Conclave of The Damn<br>